headline: Wall Street ticks to records after shaking off worries about Trump's feud with the Fed
summary: Wall Street ticked to more records Monday after bouncing back from losses taken because of worries about the worsening feud between the White House and the Federal Reserve, one that experts warn could lead to higher inflation in the future.  The Dow Jones Industrial Average recovered an early loss of nearly 500 points and added 86, or 0.2%, to its own record, while the Nasdaq composite gained 0.3%.  Walmart helped drive the U.S. stock market higher despite the worries.
